item.title: Wow USA, this one must hurt!!! “We do not want to be rich like Americans. Look how greedy they are, even trying to invade their friends. We would not sell ourselves. We know what happened to Indigenous people in Alaska and Native Americans.
item.description: Their land was taken, and they were not treated well.” — Greenlandic politician Tillie Martinussen That is not a throwaway jab, it is a full moral indictment. It flips the usual American self image on its head: wealth is not automatically admired, and power is not automatically respected. When someone says they would rather stay themselves than become “rich like Americans,” they are basically saying the brand is broken, and the history is part of the reason.

item.title: Last year someone messaged me to tell me to leave America, and accused me of being a terrorist.
item.description:
This person not only thinks all Etsy shops are US-based but also wasted time accusing me of being a terrorist based on my silly embroidery art. The thing is: I live in Europe!
This is clearly stated in my shop lol https://rebordacaoembroidery.etsy.com
How can someone be so pissed and feel threatened by this little cutie?
The best part is: I never specified a government, but the person automatically assumed I was talking about the USA.
Lots of people around the world aren’t happy with their current governments, so I make this piece in other languages too. It’s just a sassy needlework of a cat holding a “meowlotov” cocktail, not an anarchist manifesto.
Wishing you all a great week ahead!

item.title: GovBrief Today #353
item.description: Kristi Noem went on Face the Nation this morning and said ICE hadn't used chemical irritants against Minnesota protesters. When told that video contradicted her, Noem blamed the protesters. She also claimed that Minnesota Governor Tim Walz "allowed the city of Minneapolis to burn down in 2020." Millions of Americans have followed this in real time. We know Minneapolis didn't burn down because 400,000 people still live there. We know agents used pepper spray and tear gas because a federal judge reviewed the evidence and called it "uncontroverted." These are lies told to our faces. Noem is just the latest in Trump's orbit to gaslight Americans on camera. They shot a woman in the head and multiple private videos exist. They've beaten and gassed protesters exercising their First Amendment rights and still more videos exist. But they and their supporters insist that what we see and hear didn't happen. New Hampshire's Episcopal bishop believed the suffering and death he saw. Earlier this week, he ordered his clergy to finalize their wills and prepare for "a new era of martyrdom." He invoked Jonathan Daniels, a seminary student shot protecting a Black teenager in Alabama in 1965. "It may be that now is no longer the time for statements," Bishop Hirschfeld said, "but for us with our bodies to stand between the powers of this world and the most vulnerable."
